<TITLE>Family Guide to Prime Time Television</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><h1><blink>Now Available</blink></h1><p>
<h2>1996-97 Family Guide to Prime Time Television </h2></CENTER>
<img src ="/mrc/images/famsmall.gif" align="right">Parents have every reason to be frustrated with the lack of quality television programming. Hollywood is becoming more and more out-of touch with real family issues and family values. With over 90 shows airing every week on the networks alone, it's virtually impossible to know which shows promote wholesome themes -- and which ones don't.<p>

Here's what Jane Seymour of <I>Doctor Quinn, Medicine Woman</I> says.... "The <I>Family Guide</I> provides parents with the critical information needed to make intelligent viewing choices about their children's television viewing.  I commend the Parents Television Council and their efforts to get parents to take an interest in and responsibility for their children's viewing of TV."<p>

<b>The <I>Family Guide</I> contains:</b><p>
<li> Background on over 90 TV shows currently appearing on the prime time schedule.<p>
<li>Summaries of offensive (and commendable) themes promoted in these shows. <p>
<li> Color-coded recommendations: shows unsuitable for children get a "red light," while 			family-friendly programs receive a "green light." <p>
<li> Names and addresses of Hollywood decision-makers you can contact to voice your support 		of or opposition to TV's values. <p>

<center>Call <b><blink>1-800-31-GUIDE</blink></b> to order your copy by phone! </center><p>
<center>$5.95 (plus $2 for shipping & handling )<p>	
<I>California residents please add 8.25% sales tax.</I></center><br>
<p>
<I>The <a href="/mrc/ptc/"> Parents Television Council </a> is a special project of the Media Research Center and is providing the voice in Hollywood for families across America, and working daily to restore responsibility to television programming. </I><br>
<p>
(To check out last season's <I>Family Guide to Prime Time Television</I>, <a href ="/mrc/entertainment/95famgui.html">click here</a>.)

<p>
