<HEAD>
<TITLE> Timothy Lamer Biography </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">
<blockquote><h2>
<center>Timothy Lamer</center></h2><p><br>

	Timothy Lamer is director of the Free Market Project at the Media Research Center in Alexandria, Virginia. He edits a monthly newsletter, <i>MediaNomics</i>, which covers trends in how the media report on business and economics. He is also the co-author, with Burton Yale Pines, of <i>Out of Focus: Network Television and the American Economy</i> (Regnery, 1994). He has written for <i>The Weekly Standard</i> and has been interviewed by CNBC, NBC News, <i>The Philadelphia Inquirer</i>, <i>Newsweek</i>, and <i>The Washington Times</i>, among many others. He has directed studies for the Center which have been cited on the "Rush Limbaugh Show" and in such publications as the <i>Harvard Business Review, Inc.</i> magazine, <i>Investor's Business Daily</i>, <i>Forbes</i> magazine, USA Today, and <i>The Wall Street Journal </i>, among many others.

</BODY>
</HTML>
