<hr width=50%>
<!------------------------------------------------------------------->
<I>Saturday, February 8, 1997</I></CENTER><P>
<P>
Which of the following words can be defined as 
<I>The language spoken in the form in the informal idiom of a trade or profession; informal idiom?</I>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="a.html">A. Billingsgate</a>
<P>
<A HREF="b.html">B. Vernacular</a>
<P>
<A HREF="c.html">C. Cadre</a>
<!------------------------------------------------------------------->
<P>
<P>
<P>
<hr>
From <B>William F. Buckley, Jr.'s 365 Words You'd Like To Know 1995 Calendar</B><br>
Andrews and McMeel, a Universal Press Syndicate Company, Kansas City<P>
